Want to watch it on the big screen?

Here are a few ways to do that:

1) Do you have a PSP slim? If so buy the TV out cables and direct connect to your tv and play them that way. You can buy regular composite cables, svideo cables, and component cables. I recommend these:

PSP Slim Component Cable (games too): &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.amazon.com/PSP-Slim-Component-Cable-Xbox-360/dp/B00149S0H6/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.amazon.com/PSP-Slim-Component-Cable-Xbox-360/dp/B00149S0H6/&lt;/a&gt;

PSP S-Video/AV Cable (video only): &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.amazon.com/PSP-S-Video-AV-Cable-Sony/dp/B0015SKP5Q/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.amazon.com/PSP-S-Video-AV-Cable-Sony/dp/B0015SKP5Q/&lt;/a&gt;

2) Do you have an XBOX 360 and a PSP? Hook your PSP to your XBOX 360 via the USB Mini-B cable. Go to the media blade on your 360, select videos, change source, select portable device, navigate to your video.

3) If for some reason you don't have a PSP and you do have an XBOX 360 then you can just put the video files on any USB device and just connect them to your XBOX in the same manner as above.

4) You can also stream the video to your XBOX 360 using Windows Media player 11 or uShare on Linux. To stream via Windows Media Player 11 to XBOX 360 follow this guide: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://owlet.spaces.live.com/blog/cns!D48B90C1DDF5D401!297.entry&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://owlet.spaces.live.com/blog/cns!D48B90C1DDF5D401!297.entry&lt;/a&gt;

5) Watch via XBMC on your XBOX or Linux HTPC: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://xbmc.org/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://xbmc.org/&lt;/a&gt;

6) There is most likely a way to stream this to a PS3 or play via USB device also, but I don't own one, so I can't advise on how to do that.

7) Use a Popcorn Hour A-110 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.popcornhour.com/onlinestore/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.popcornhour.com/onlinestore/&lt;/a&gt;

8) Stream to your PS3 or Xbox 360 using TVersity, refer to: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://tversity.com/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://tversity.com/&lt;/a&gt;

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Note: playing mpeg 4 videos on Xbox 360 requires the Dec 2007 video update.  You may also need to download the optional video codec pack.  Refer to: &lt;a href=&quot;
http://blogs.msdn.com/xboxteam/archive/2007/11/30/december-2007-video-playback-faq.aspx&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://blogs.msdn.com/xboxteam/archive/2007/11/30/december-2007-video-playback-faq.aspx&lt;/a&gt; 

